card1: Ukrainian Minecraft server that was founded spontaneously, but quickly gained popularity. A unique product known for its stability and responsiveness. Fast updates and an unconventional approach were the reasons for its adoration.
card2: Program for registering a whole array of Web3 keys and searching for wallets with balances. The program didn't show effectiveness, but skills in using API requests became the foundation for future products.
card3: A virus that didn't harm anyone. Keylogger, cracker, miner, trojan, all under one hood. A simple program that almost caused trouble. Experience in developing malicious software - I've got it :)
card4: An automation service for big and small. Suitable for any MMORPG or other in-game organization. Custom functionality based on the 4C principle (create your own website). Modular development allows for quality selection of necessary features, and authentication through Discord helps maintain high security and manage permissions right from the application.
